today remember with awe

796
00:45:20,684 --> 00:45:23,619
the kind of respect
their relatives were afforded,

797
00:45:23,687 --> 00:45:26,121
especially by white Southerners.

798
00:45:26,190 --> 00:45:28,124
MAN: There's a story
of my granddad.

799
00:45:28,192 --> 00:45:30,626
He went to the local
tractor shop there

800
00:45:30,694 --> 00:45:32,628
in Cleveland, Mississippi,

801
00:45:32,696 --> 00:45:34,687
and he stood in the back.

802
00:45:34,765 --> 00:45:37,199
There was this young guy
that not long had been

803
00:45:37,267 --> 00:45:40,236
working behind the counter,
and he saw my granddad
standing there,

804
00:45:40,304 --> 00:45:42,238
and he said, "Nigger,
take your hat off!"

805
00:45:42,306 --> 00:45:45,207
And so my granddaddy
just stood there,

806
00:45:45,275 --> 00:45:48,005
and before he could
say it the next time,
he said, "Nigger- ♪

807
00:45:48,078 --> 00:45:50,012
Said, "Come here,"
they said,

808
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:52,674
"That's not a nigger.
He's from Mound Bayou."

809
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:54,274
[Both laugh]

810
00:45:54,351 --> 00:45:57,286
GATES: Isaiah believed
that only by living apart

811
00:45:57,354 --> 00:46:00,983
from white people could
black Southerners thrive.

812
00:46:01,058 --> 00:46:04,550
But his all-black town also
appeased white Southerners

813
00:46:04,628 --> 00:46:08,064
increasingly determined
to impose racial segregation

814
00:46:08,132 --> 00:46:09,622
on the South.

815
00:46:09,700 --> 00:46:12,328
White America did not
fear Mound Bayou.
Mm-mmm.

816
00:46:12,402 --> 00:46:16,304
Montgomery had already
made clear in various ways

817
00:46:16,373 --> 00:46:21,106
that he had no intentions
of being a political problem.

818
00:46:21,178 --> 00:46:23,612
That is, he had no intention
of claiming his rights

819
00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:26,615
beyond the confines
of building his business

820
00:46:26,683 --> 00:46:29,015
and his world
in Mound Bayou.

821
00:46:29,086 --> 00:46:33,523
