Negro reader.
Yeah, exactly, right?

902
00:50:49,813 --> 00:50:52,611
As if they would have
a Negro meter or
something like that.

903
00:50:52,682 --> 00:50:54,582
It's patently absurd.

904
00:50:56,686 --> 00:50:58,620
Plessy gets his ticket,

905
00:50:58,688 --> 00:51:00,952
he goes right past
the colored car,

906
00:51:01,024 --> 00:51:04,721
sits in the white car,
and that's when a
plain-cloth es officer

907
00:51:04,795 --> 00:51:07,491
warns him to get off
the train and, when he
doesn't move,

908
00:51:07,564 --> 00:51:09,498
arrests him
and takes him off.

909
00:51:09,566 --> 00:51:14,003
GATES: The case did make it all
the way to the Supreme Court,

910
00:51:14,071 --> 00:51:18,508
but the Justices didn't do what
Plessy and his backers hoped.

911
00:51:18,575 --> 00:51:20,668
In a momentous decision
that would shape

912
00:51:20,744 --> 00:51:22,678
the next half-century,

913
00:51:22,746 --> 00:51:26,773
they upheld Louisiana's
segregation law.

914
00:51:26,850 --> 00:51:29,546
The Supreme Court decided

915
00:51:29,619 --> 00:51:32,053
that separate but equal

916
00:51:32,122 --> 00:51:34,056
was the law of the land.

917
00:51:34,124 --> 00:51:36,058
Justice might be blind,

918
00:51:36,126 --> 00:51:38,560
but the United States
Constitution

919
00:51:38,628 --> 00:51:41,791
would no longer be
color-blind.

920
00:51:43,900 --> 00:51:46,334
The Plessy decision dealt
the final blow

921
00:51:46,403 --> 00:51:50,305
